						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">No date</hi></p>						

						<p>States in Tamil verse that the eight celestial elephants (<hi rend="italic">ashṭa-dig-gajas</hi>) rested at the presenting (building) of the eight elephants (in stone) by <hi rend="bold">Chakrarāya</hi> to the god; that the celestial elephants were held by the <hi rend="italic">dikpālas</hi> lest they run away in fear of these (stone) elephants.</p>						

